<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1459,1700]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,304,1459,1484]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Distribution.</emphasis>
South of Europe, reaching central Europe to 
<collectingCountry box="[834,970,1460,1484]" name="Switzerland" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Switzerland</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[985,1086,1460,1484]" name="Slovakia" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Slovakia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1100,1199,1461,1485]" name="Hungary" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Hungary</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[1263,1356,1460,1484]" name="Ukraine" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
, in the east through 
<collectingCountry box="[295,375,1495,1519]" name="Turkey" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Turkey</collectingCountry>
to Turkestan, present also in North Africa (
<bibRefCitation author="Warncke" box="[863,1029,1495,1519]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refString="Warncke, K. (1992) Die Westpalaarktischen Arten der Bienengattung Sphecodes Latr. (Hymenoptera, Apidae, Halictinae). Bericht der Naturforschenden Gesellschaft Augsburg, 52, 9 - 64." type="journal article" year="1992">
Warncke 
<number box="[970,1029,1495,1519]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1992.0">1992</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Amiet" box="[1040,1240,1495,1520]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refString="Amiet, F., Muller, A. &amp; Neumeyer, R. (1999) Hymenoptera Apidae. 2. Teil: Gattungen Colletes, Dufourea, Hylaeus, Nomia, Nomioides, Rhophitoides, Rophites, Sphecodes, Systropha. Fauna Helvetica 4. Centre Suisse de Cartographie de la Faune &amp; Schweitzerische Entomologische Gesellschaft, Luzern, 219 pp." type="book" year="1999">
Amiet 
<emphasis box="[1118,1174,1496,1520]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[1180,1240,1495,1519]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1999.0">1999</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1459,1700]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,297,1531,1556]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Biology.</emphasis>
Species of warm sites, especially sand dunes; quite common in various warm biotopes in southern Europe. In central Europe it is rare. Abundant in extensive sandy sites such as military training areas or larger sand quarries. Hosts unconfirmed. It was observed in association with 
<taxonomicName authority="Walckener" authorityName="Walckener" box="[913,1295,1604,1628]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Halictus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="compressus">
<emphasis box="[913,1148,1604,1628]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Halictus compressus</emphasis>
(Walckener)
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[1338,1436,1605,1629]" name="Hungary" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Hungary</collectingCountry>
(own observations); 
<taxonomicName authority="Bluthgen" authorityName="Bluthgen" box="[385,692,1639,1664]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Halictus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="langobardicus">
<emphasis box="[385,582,1640,1664]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">H. langobardicus</emphasis>
Blüthgen
</taxonomicName>
is another likely host. 
<bibRefCitation author="Bluthgen" box="[958,1144,1639,1663]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refString="Bluthgen, P. (1934) Die Wirte der Palaarktischen Sphecodes - Arten. Zeitschrift Wissenschaftlicher Insekten-Biologie, 27, 33 - 42, 61 - 66. Bluthgen, P. (1935) Halictus, Nomioides und Sphecodes, pp. 360 - 367. In: Popov, V. V. (ed.) Beitrage zur Bienenfauna von Tadzhikistan. Trudy Tajikskoy Bazy Akademie Nauk SSSR, 5, 1 - 408." type="book chapter" year="1934">
Blüthgen (
<number box="[1078,1136,1639,1663]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1934.0">1934</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
recorded 
<taxonomicName authority="F. Morawitz" authorityName="F. Morawitz" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Halictus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="patellatus">
<emphasis box="[1260,1406,1640,1664]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">H. patellatus</emphasis>
F. Morawitz
</taxonomicName>
as the likely host.
</paragraph>
